WEBVTT

00:05.505 --> 00:07.072
(THUNDER BOOMING)

00:07.307 --> 00:09.808
<i>♪</i>

00:21.788 --> 00:24.223
(SCREAMING)

00:24.225 --> 00:26.525
<i>♪</i>

00:39.472 --> 00:40.439
(GROANING)

00:40.441 --> 00:43.675
Why aren't my dad's
plants growing?

00:44.044 --> 00:47.046
Your dad's plants aren't
growing 'cause they're dead.

00:47.048 --> 00:48.781
And not good dead like you.

00:48.783 --> 00:50.883
Dead like dead and gone.

00:50.885 --> 00:52.284
(COUGHING)

00:52.286 --> 00:53.252
Ooh!

00:53.254 --> 00:54.686
This plant is growing!

00:54.688 --> 00:56.488
(SCREAMING)

00:58.124 --> 00:59.591
Or making a run for it.

00:59.593 --> 01:01.026
No, no, no.

01:01.028 --> 01:02.428
No, no, no, no.
They can't be dead!

01:02.430 --> 01:06.198
I promised my dad
I'd take care of them
while he's away.

01:06.200 --> 01:10.836
Maybe watering with
acid rain isn't your
best choice.

01:10.838 --> 01:11.603
Urgh!

01:11.605 --> 01:15.007
I don't get it.
I totally have a green thumb.

01:15.009 --> 01:18.377
Same. Though mine is probably
from gangrene.

01:18.379 --> 01:23.282
Ew. You should really see
Dr. Gillman about that!

01:24.250 --> 01:25.117
(GASPING)

01:25.119 --> 01:28.420
I can get new plants
from Quasimodo's garden!

01:28.422 --> 01:30.022
My dad will never know.

01:30.024 --> 01:32.391
Um, isn't your dad a psycho?

01:32.393 --> 01:34.126
I think you mean a "psychic."

01:34.128 --> 01:37.362
Either way, let's hope
he doesn't find out!

01:37.364 --> 01:38.997
Come on, Wendy!

01:38.999 --> 01:42.234
(LAUGHING)
This'll be a fresh start.

01:42.236 --> 01:44.503
I'm taking care of
another living thing,

01:44.505 --> 01:45.938
even if it kills me!

01:45.940 --> 01:48.407
Like you killed that
cockroach in your pocket?

01:48.409 --> 01:52.611
Margaret is not dead!
She's shy.

01:52.613 --> 01:54.780
(SINGING FRENCH NATIONAL
ANTHEM WITH LAS)

01:54.782 --> 01:58.817
Whoop, they goes. And...
<i>♪ La, la</i>

01:58.819 --> 02:00.486
Whoop!
<i>♪ And la, la</i>

02:00.488 --> 02:01.653
Hop! Hop!

02:01.655 --> 02:04.656
Whoa!
(VOCALIZING)

02:04.658 --> 02:07.126
Okay!

02:07.293 --> 02:08.727
(SNIFFING)

02:10.096 --> 02:12.264
(SNIFFING) Ah!

02:12.266 --> 02:14.833
(CLEARING THROAT)
Quasi?

02:14.835 --> 02:16.869
Wha?
I need some plants.

02:16.871 --> 02:17.970
<i>Bien sur.</i>

02:17.972 --> 02:23.308
I have Poison Ivy,
Dead Rabbit Foot Fern, and uh,

02:23.310 --> 02:24.143
oh, Daisies.

02:24.145 --> 02:26.044
What about...
(HIGH-PITCHED SHRIEKING)

02:26.046 --> 02:28.881
No! I don't grow...
(HIGH-PITCHED SHRIEKING)

02:28.883 --> 02:30.749
...anymore.
Way too annoying.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.385
I mean, you can't
break that egg!

02:33.387 --> 02:37.956
This is a very bad egg.

02:37.958 --> 02:40.292
But it hasn't even
had a chance.

02:40.294 --> 02:41.360
To do what?

02:41.362 --> 02:43.795
I don't know.
Be an egg.

02:43.797 --> 02:46.798
It's so cute.

02:46.800 --> 02:49.168
(GASPING)
I've got it!

02:49.170 --> 02:50.102
I'll raise it!

02:50.104 --> 02:53.972
What better way to show
I'm responsi...ooh!

02:53.974 --> 02:56.675
I tested it with
my taste receptors

02:56.677 --> 02:58.443
and zat is a rotten egg!

02:58.445 --> 03:01.647
That's my spit
and boogers right there.

03:01.649 --> 03:03.682
It will eat you when
it hatches, you know.

03:03.684 --> 03:06.118
Eggs don't eat vampires.

03:06.120 --> 03:07.953
Or...anything.

03:07.955 --> 03:11.557
Hah! That egg will have you
for Scareday Brunch!

03:11.559 --> 03:13.692
Don't worry, as long as
that egg is with Mavis,

03:13.694 --> 03:15.460
it's as good as dead.

03:15.462 --> 03:16.962
(SCREAMING)

03:16.964 --> 03:18.230
Uh, bye!

03:18.232 --> 03:21.366
Saperlipopette!

03:26.339 --> 03:28.874
Don't you think of making
a break for it.

03:28.876 --> 03:32.844
I'm taking care of you,
if it's the last thing I do.

03:32.846 --> 03:36.949
Hmm. I'd better egg-proof
my room a bit.

03:38.685 --> 03:40.919
<i>♪</i>

03:51.564 --> 03:53.165
There, that should do it.

03:53.167 --> 03:56.235
Room service!
How would you like your egg?

03:56.237 --> 03:58.103
Fried? Poached?

03:58.105 --> 04:01.039
Scrambled?
(LAUGHS)

04:01.041 --> 04:04.076
Quasi, stop trying
to poach my egg!

04:04.078 --> 04:06.044
Poached!
My specialty.

04:06.046 --> 04:10.282
Breakfast is the most
important meal of the day!

04:11.618 --> 04:13.151
(LAUGHING)

04:13.153 --> 04:14.853
Go away!

04:14.855 --> 04:17.089
Bah!
You'll be sorry!

04:17.091 --> 04:19.491
Okay! We've gotta
keep you warm.

04:19.493 --> 04:22.728
Hey, we're going bowling!
You in?

04:22.730 --> 04:25.530
We drew straws.
I'm the ball.

04:25.532 --> 04:27.399
Um, yeah, I, uh...

04:27.401 --> 04:28.600
I wish I could, but ah,

04:28.602 --> 04:31.937
I got a whole day of
sitting ahead of me.

04:32.405 --> 04:33.972
Is this real life?

04:33.974 --> 04:36.308
(CLUCKING)
All wrong!

04:36.310 --> 04:38.243
(CLUCKING)
Wings up!

04:38.245 --> 04:39.811
(CLUCKING)
Legs back!

04:39.813 --> 04:41.313
(CLUCKING)
Carry on!

04:41.315 --> 04:42.381
(CLUCKING)

04:42.383 --> 04:43.415
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY)

04:43.417 --> 04:46.285
Seems I, uh,
wasn't doing it right.

04:46.287 --> 04:48.654
Ha-ha!
(VOCALIZING)

04:48.656 --> 04:51.890
I must get that bad egg!

04:51.892 --> 04:53.025
Mavis!

04:53.027 --> 04:56.928
Shh!
Weggsley is sleeping.

04:56.930 --> 04:58.563
You...named it?

04:58.565 --> 05:01.800
Aw, Weggsley is
so darling when he sleeps.

05:01.802 --> 05:04.136
Just look at that...face?

05:04.138 --> 05:05.904
I know, right?

05:05.906 --> 05:08.273
It has no face.
It's just an egg.

05:08.275 --> 05:10.676
Maybe to you!
(COOING)

05:10.678 --> 05:14.112
Yeah, pretty sure it looks
that way to everybody.

05:14.114 --> 05:15.447
That and crazy.

05:15.449 --> 05:16.848
Do you think when
Weggsley wakes up,

05:16.850 --> 05:18.350
he might want to
play egg sport?

05:18.352 --> 05:20.185
I thought you were
going bowling.

05:20.187 --> 05:22.187
That didn't last long.

05:25.191 --> 05:26.692
So long, suckers!

05:26.694 --> 05:30.395
Tell the Draculas
I'm on vacation!

05:30.397 --> 05:33.665
Oh, BTW,
Cheryl's on vacation.

05:33.667 --> 05:35.400
(SIGHING)
Fine.

05:35.402 --> 05:37.135
How do you play egg sport?

05:37.137 --> 05:39.004
Alright, you kick
the egg around

05:39.006 --> 05:42.140
until it breaks into a million
pieces, then you eat it.

05:42.142 --> 05:43.842
You know, egg sport!

05:43.844 --> 05:45.544
Egg sport.

05:45.546 --> 05:48.680
(GASPING)
You monsters!

05:48.948 --> 05:51.283
Uh, duh.

05:52.685 --> 05:54.720
Huh?
(YELPING)

05:54.722 --> 05:57.589
QUASI: <i>Zut alors!</i>
<i>You are not the egg!</i>

05:57.591 --> 06:00.325
WENDY:
Ooh, cool vent.

06:00.327 --> 06:06.064
Don't you worry,
little Weggsley,
I'll take care of you.

06:06.066 --> 06:08.266
(SIGHING CONTENTEDLY)

06:08.268 --> 06:09.668
(CRACKING)

06:09.670 --> 06:12.704
Holy rabies!
He's hatching!

06:13.740 --> 06:17.209
Weggsley!
You're a real boy!

06:18.611 --> 06:20.812
<i>♪</i>

06:27.520 --> 06:29.688
(LAUGHING)

06:30.990 --> 06:32.090
PEDRO:
Hey, Mavis!

06:32.092 --> 06:35.494
New plan: we're goin'
looking for Wendy. Wanna come?

06:35.496 --> 06:40.065
She's missing?
Or hiding! We just don't know.

06:40.067 --> 06:45.537
I wish I could help, but...
guess who hatched!

06:47.507 --> 06:52.778
I have a greater purpose
in my undead life now.

06:52.780 --> 06:53.979
Why?
You did it.

06:53.981 --> 06:56.415
You proved you could keep
something alive,

06:56.417 --> 06:58.483
as weird as it is.

06:58.485 --> 07:01.019
It's really not
about that at all.

07:01.021 --> 07:03.221
But it's kind of
about that, right?

07:03.223 --> 07:05.157
Okay.
It's about that, right?

07:05.159 --> 07:07.292
I mean...
It started out that way,
right?

07:07.294 --> 07:10.195
Okay!
It started out that way.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.663
But look, he needs me.

07:11.665 --> 07:17.235
When you have an egg
with legs one day,
you'll understand.

07:17.237 --> 07:18.837
Is this real life?

07:18.839 --> 07:23.308
Mavis, you heard Quasi.
That dude is a bad egg!

07:23.310 --> 07:25.243
No, he's not.
He is the sweetest,

07:25.245 --> 07:29.147
cutest egg
you could ever ask for.

07:29.248 --> 07:30.415
(CRASHING)

07:30.417 --> 07:32.317
(WHISPERING)
Let's go find Wendy.

07:32.319 --> 07:35.821
"All the king's ghouls
and undead men

07:35.823 --> 07:38.190
"couldn't put Humpty together
again."

07:38.192 --> 07:43.862
Wow. I can't believe
I just read that to you.
Sorry.

07:45.097 --> 07:46.031
(LAUGHING)

07:46.033 --> 07:49.835
Aw, you want to play
creep-a-boo.

07:49.837 --> 07:52.137
(LAUGHING)

07:52.139 --> 07:54.873
(LAUGHING AND GROWLING)

07:54.875 --> 07:57.476
Creep-a-boo!

07:57.844 --> 08:00.946
How long did I cover
my eyes for?

08:00.948 --> 08:03.815
Weggsley!

08:03.817 --> 08:06.084
Wendy!

08:06.086 --> 08:07.786
Hi, Hank!

08:07.788 --> 08:10.856
(STRAINING)
We found you.

08:10.858 --> 08:11.857
Oh, was I lost?

08:11.859 --> 08:14.726
Because it has happened
to me before without
me knowing.

08:14.728 --> 08:17.596
Wah!
Ugh. Who's the giant rat?

08:17.598 --> 08:18.763
Uh, Quasimodo?

08:18.765 --> 08:20.899
No, we're talking about
the other giant...

08:20.901 --> 08:23.268
(ALL SCREAMING)

08:23.703 --> 08:25.437
(GASPING)

08:25.439 --> 08:27.339
Weggsley, there you are!

08:27.341 --> 08:28.740
(SCREAMING)

08:28.742 --> 08:33.311
Oh, careful!
You'll turn yourself
into a chopped egg salad!

08:33.313 --> 08:36.014
Nightshade vegetables
for a snack?

08:36.015 --> 08:37.916
You are either
a very healthy eater

08:37.918 --> 08:40.719
or you are stalling
before bedtime!

08:40.721 --> 08:42.721
Come back here!

08:48.728 --> 08:50.362
Now stay put.

08:50.364 --> 08:52.364
QUASI:
Look! <i>Ze</i> kitchen!

08:52.366 --> 08:54.866
(ALL PANTING)

08:54.868 --> 08:56.034
Aw, did you guys come here

08:56.036 --> 08:58.904
because you're worried
about Weggsley too?

08:58.906 --> 09:00.639
Uh, sure.

09:00.641 --> 09:03.074
Also, we were running
from a giant rat.

09:03.076 --> 09:04.342
Really big.
Like huge.

09:04.344 --> 09:06.278
I thought
we were chasing it.

09:06.280 --> 09:07.746
Uh, Mavis?

09:07.748 --> 09:11.650
You know how you said
you'd take care of
another living creature

09:11.652 --> 09:13.885
even if it killed you?
Uh-huh!

09:13.887 --> 09:17.088
Pretty sure the killing
part is about to happen.

09:17.090 --> 09:19.758
Oh, he's just playing
make-believe!

09:19.760 --> 09:22.994
Yeah, well, it's about time
you start to believe believe

09:22.996 --> 09:24.896
'cause that egg
gonna cook you!

09:24.898 --> 09:26.565
It is a bad egg!

09:26.567 --> 09:28.033
Get out of there, Mavis!

09:28.035 --> 09:30.902
Ah! Holy rabies!

09:32.705 --> 09:34.806
He flies too?

09:34.808 --> 09:37.175
I told you
he's a fast learner!

09:38.477 --> 09:40.278
<i>C'est pas</i> possible!

09:40.280 --> 09:42.714
Oh, it's possible.

09:42.716 --> 09:45.317
(MAVIS PANTING)

09:47.320 --> 09:48.386
(LAUGHING)

09:48.388 --> 09:52.824
I am beating this egg
once and for all!

09:52.826 --> 09:58.029
Sorry, Quasi, but he's still
my weird flying egg baby!

09:58.031 --> 09:59.764
Ooh!

10:00.466 --> 10:02.400
(SCREAMING)

10:06.839 --> 10:07.872
(CRASHING)

10:07.874 --> 10:09.574
QUASI:
<i>Saperlipopette!</i>

10:09.576 --> 10:11.242
MAVIS: Ah!

10:13.179 --> 10:15.747
(MAVIS SCREAMING)

10:17.550 --> 10:19.851
(GULPING) Now what?

10:19.986 --> 10:23.622
We'll put something
really nice on your
tombstone, Mavis!

10:23.624 --> 10:25.624
"Here Lies the bestest
friend ever."

10:25.626 --> 10:29.594
Aw, you are just
the sweetest, Wendy!

10:29.596 --> 10:30.795
Killer egg?

10:30.797 --> 10:32.597
Oh, right.

10:32.999 --> 10:34.699
(ROARING)

10:35.935 --> 10:38.336
Uh-oh.
Whoa!

10:42.708 --> 10:45.844
Weggsley!
(SOBBING)

10:47.680 --> 10:49.514
<i>En guarde!</i>

10:49.516 --> 10:50.382
(SIGHING)

10:50.384 --> 10:53.251
I guess he was
a bad egg after all.

10:53.253 --> 10:56.121
If only somebody
had warned me.

10:56.123 --> 10:58.056
(SCREAMING)

10:58.058 --> 11:01.793
But on the plus side,
my dad is going to be
so proud

11:01.795 --> 11:04.963
of how huge his
Venus flytrap has grown!

11:04.965 --> 11:07.232
(STOMACH GURGLING)

11:09.769 --> 11:12.804
Well, I still have Margaret.

11:12.806 --> 11:17.142
Nope, I've been
dead for weeks.

11:17.144 --> 11:19.477
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY)

11:25.551 --> 11:27.619
<i>♪</i>

11:30.456 --> 11:31.589
(STRAINING)

11:31.591 --> 11:33.992
Okay,
that was a lot of work,

11:33.994 --> 11:38.029
but we can finally
watch human TV again.

11:38.031 --> 11:39.998
I may be grossed out
by the sight, smell,

11:40.000 --> 11:43.702
and hairdos of humans,
but, man, do I love their TV.

11:43.704 --> 11:47.305
Huh, I didn't realize
you knew how to hook up
cable, Mavis.

11:47.307 --> 11:51.009
It's actually pretty simple,
if you have the right tools,

11:51.011 --> 11:53.411
which I do not.

11:53.413 --> 11:54.979
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING,
MAVIS COUGHING)

11:54.981 --> 11:58.483
I still can't believe
your Aunt Lydia's okay
with us watching it.

11:58.485 --> 12:00.652
(LAUGHING)
Oh, she isn't.

12:00.654 --> 12:04.622
If she finds out,
she'll probably eat
our souls.

12:05.091 --> 12:06.157
Now, who's ready

12:06.159 --> 12:10.061
for the final episode
of <i>Hotel Pennsylvania?</i>

12:10.063 --> 12:12.297
(CHEERING)

12:13.032 --> 12:14.632
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

12:14.634 --> 12:17.635
<i>♪ Sometimes in life,</i>
<i>you can start to feel</i>

12:17.637 --> 12:21.573
<i>♪ Like you got no room,</i>
<i>like you just can't deal</i>

12:21.575 --> 12:24.576
<i>♪ But you can pack your bags,</i>
<i>you can check right in</i>

12:24.578 --> 12:29.914
<i>♪ 'Cause new adventures</i>
<i>are about to begin!</i>

12:31.817 --> 12:33.551
<i>♪ So make some room for me!</i>

12:33.553 --> 12:35.086
(CLUCKING)
What's that?

12:35.088 --> 12:37.555
<i>♪ And make some room for me!</i>

12:37.557 --> 12:39.557
(CLUCKING) TV?

12:39.559 --> 12:41.659
<i>♪ And make some room for me</i>

12:41.661 --> 12:43.795
<i>♪ And me and me</i>

12:43.797 --> 12:47.232
<i>♪ At Hotel Pennsylvania</i>

12:47.234 --> 12:51.236
Is it me or do Davis,
Tank, Penny, and Petra

12:51.238 --> 12:54.339
seem, like, really familiar?

12:54.341 --> 12:55.039
Nope.

12:55.041 --> 12:57.942
Don't think so.
Clearly just you.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.645
(ALL SCREAMING)

13:00.647 --> 13:04.415
Cable seems okay.
I wonder what happ...

13:04.417 --> 13:06.184
(CLEARING THROAT)

13:06.186 --> 13:07.452
Aunt Lydia! Oh!

13:07.454 --> 13:09.120
We were just trying
to figure out

13:09.122 --> 13:11.890
what this weird
cable-y thingy is. Huh?

13:11.892 --> 13:14.025
What are you just babbling
about there, Mavis?

13:14.027 --> 13:16.127
You just set it up for us
to watch human TV, huh?

13:16.129 --> 13:19.864
I hope you got your
fill of that disgusting
human program

13:19.866 --> 13:22.267
because I have
personally disposed of

13:22.269 --> 13:25.370
every television in the hotel.

13:25.372 --> 13:26.905
Mark my words...

13:26.907 --> 13:30.041
none of you will ever watch TV

13:30.043 --> 13:32.243
in this hotel again!

13:32.245 --> 13:35.246
'Cept on
our birthdays, right?

13:35.248 --> 13:37.148
Ever!

13:41.320 --> 13:42.821
Diane.

13:42.823 --> 13:45.523
(CLUCKING MOCKINGLY)

13:46.258 --> 13:47.258
(GROANING)

13:47.260 --> 13:50.261
I guess we're never gonna see
the last episode of <i>Hotel P.</i>

13:50.263 --> 13:51.796
Ah!
That's not good.

13:51.798 --> 13:53.331
I heard you can
get real sick

13:53.333 --> 13:55.733
if you miss the final
episode of a show.

13:55.735 --> 13:57.769
It's called the
don't-sees disease.

13:57.771 --> 14:00.672
That is so not a real thing.

14:00.674 --> 14:03.708
Of course the don't-sees
is a real thing!

14:03.710 --> 14:07.979
It's just not in text books
or journals.

14:07.981 --> 14:10.982
Also, I may have just
named it yesterday.

14:10.984 --> 14:12.684
Take this case.

14:12.686 --> 14:16.788
He used to be twenty feet tall
and as smelly as a Minotaur.

14:16.790 --> 14:22.026
But then he missed the last
episode of <i>My Three Huns.</i>

14:22.028 --> 14:26.764
(WEAKLY) Barbara!
What happened to Barbara?

14:30.236 --> 14:32.470
As you can see from
this chart I just drew,

14:32.472 --> 14:36.608
missing the last episode
of a TV show turns
normal monsters

14:36.610 --> 14:40.111
into puddles
at an alarming rate.

14:40.113 --> 14:44.182
But, ah, that won't happen
to us, will it, Dr. Gillman?

14:44.184 --> 14:47.685
Not as long as you follow
this prescription...

14:47.687 --> 14:50.521
to the letter!

14:50.523 --> 14:52.123
"Watch TV."

14:52.125 --> 14:54.993
No one ever said
the road to recovery
would be a smooth one.

14:54.995 --> 14:55.793
(SNORING)

14:55.795 --> 15:00.131
Yes! Now we've just gotta give
this to Aunt Lydia and...

15:00.133 --> 15:02.100
Lydia! Ah!

15:02.102 --> 15:04.769
You were never here.

15:05.304 --> 15:09.474
So, not only are we gonna miss
the last episode of <i>Hotel P,</i>

15:09.476 --> 15:12.543
we're gonna be puddles, too?
Awesome.

15:12.545 --> 15:13.778
(THEME SONG PLAYING FAINTLY)

15:13.780 --> 15:16.147
It's like I can still hear
the theme song in my head.

15:16.149 --> 15:18.549
(GASPING)
What if that's a symptom?

15:18.551 --> 15:20.051
No wait!
I hear it too!

15:20.053 --> 15:22.754
It's coming from
the Cartwright house!

15:22.756 --> 15:24.989
(THEME SONG PLAYING FAINTLY)

15:25.524 --> 15:29.694
66 episodes in a row!
New record!

15:29.696 --> 15:31.796
Ow, ow!

15:32.364 --> 15:34.365
Are you sure this
is a good idea?

15:34.367 --> 15:35.967
If Lydia finds out...

15:35.969 --> 15:37.702
But she won't find out.

15:37.704 --> 15:40.405
There's no way Diane
is following us.

15:40.407 --> 15:41.706
It's worth the risk.

15:41.708 --> 15:44.175
I am not down with
that gooey puddle look.

15:44.177 --> 15:47.512
Plus, I gotta know what
happens to my girl Petra.

15:47.514 --> 15:49.847
ANNOUNCER:
<i>This week on</i>
<i>Hotel Pennsylvania,</i>

15:49.849 --> 15:53.418
<i>Davis checks in a Mister...</i>
<i>Bank Robbertson?</i>

15:53.420 --> 15:57.388
No way!
He was on the last
episode too!

15:57.390 --> 15:58.756
(ALARM BEEPING)

15:58.758 --> 16:00.692
Sweet chili heat!

16:00.694 --> 16:01.826
Is it really 6:00 a.m.?

16:01.828 --> 16:04.429
Our special guest is gonna
be here any minute!

16:04.431 --> 16:07.198
Mavis, maybe
we should go, too.

16:07.200 --> 16:08.800
It's getting
pretty bright out

16:08.802 --> 16:10.935
and, I mean,
the humans and all...

16:10.937 --> 16:15.173
What? We're finally
watching the last episode!

16:15.175 --> 16:18.176
I will not let you succumb
to the sickness.

16:18.178 --> 16:20.445
Dibs on the lawn chair!
(CLUCKING)

16:20.447 --> 16:24.349
Diane?
But how did you...

16:24.351 --> 16:25.883
(CLUCKING)

16:25.885 --> 16:27.885
I see what's going on here.

16:27.887 --> 16:29.420
(CLUCKING) You do?

16:29.422 --> 16:31.589
You were following us
this whole time!

16:31.591 --> 16:34.359
Lemmie guess, now you're gonna
tell Lydia what we did

16:34.361 --> 16:37.695
and she'll make us
clean out the Cerberus Pit.

16:37.697 --> 16:41.299
Bwak-bwak-busted.

16:41.467 --> 16:44.068
(PANTING)
I feel like...

16:44.070 --> 16:46.137
a big moist towelette!

16:46.139 --> 16:48.840
It must be the
don't-sees taking hold!

16:48.842 --> 16:51.476
Tell my burrito guy
I love him!

16:51.478 --> 16:55.680
I'm dripping too! Mavis,
we gotta find a TV stat!

16:55.682 --> 17:00.651
I still don't get how
Diane followed us
without us knowing.

17:00.653 --> 17:04.756
Unless, what if
she was already there?

17:04.758 --> 17:05.957
Uh, she was?

17:05.959 --> 17:08.393
I mean, what if
she wasn't spying?

17:08.395 --> 17:10.395
What if she was there for
another reason

17:10.396 --> 17:12.195
and just got lucky?

17:12.198 --> 17:15.199
It's just like that
<i>Hotel Pennsylvania</i> episode,

17:15.201 --> 17:17.068
<i>"Catch Me If You Cantaloupe."</i>

17:17.069 --> 17:19.604
<i>Davis and the gang</i>
<i>snuck into the lobby</i>

17:19.606 --> 17:23.040
<i>to read the Monster Comics</i>
<i>that Uncle Sid forbid them to.</i>

17:23.042 --> 17:23.974
<i>But at the same time,</i>

17:23.977 --> 17:28.046
<i>Ryan was stealing</i>
<i>Sid's prized cantaloupe</i>
<i>from the front desk!</i>

17:28.048 --> 17:31.983
<i>Then, Davis assumes Ryan</i>
<i>was spying on them</i>

17:31.985 --> 17:34.352
<i>and Ryan,</i>
<i>he just goes with it!</i>

17:34.354 --> 17:35.486
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

17:35.488 --> 17:38.623
No, not even close, Wendy.

17:38.625 --> 17:41.292
That show is fictional. Duh.

17:41.294 --> 17:42.693
This here is real life.

17:42.695 --> 17:44.562
Who's even heard of
"cantaloupe?"

17:44.564 --> 17:45.363
True.

17:45.365 --> 17:49.700
I think maybe it's time
we turned the tables
on that bird.

17:49.702 --> 17:51.502
Come on, guys!

17:51.504 --> 17:53.638
(CLUCKING)

17:55.474 --> 17:57.075
(CLUCKING)

17:57.077 --> 17:58.843
(HORN BLARING)

18:00.579 --> 18:04.082
Diane really is sneaking
over to the human house.

18:04.084 --> 18:04.982
But why?

18:04.984 --> 18:06.651
And why would
she take the 95 bus?

18:06.653 --> 18:09.554
The number 2
is way more direct.

18:13.659 --> 18:16.327
Where'd she go? We were right
on her tail feathers!

18:16.329 --> 18:21.466
Wait! Is losing people one
of the signs of the
don't-sees?

18:21.468 --> 18:23.935
Mavis!
(ROOSTER CROWING)

18:23.937 --> 18:26.270
(CROWING)

18:26.272 --> 18:28.372
No way!

18:28.374 --> 18:29.807
You're back!

18:29.809 --> 18:31.909
Humans!
We gotta warn her!

18:31.911 --> 18:34.112
It's too late.
She's a goner.

18:34.114 --> 18:35.713
I can't look.

18:35.715 --> 18:37.415
(CLUCKING)

18:37.417 --> 18:39.117
ALL: Huh?

18:39.119 --> 18:40.518
(CLUCKING)

18:40.520 --> 18:41.586
(LAUGHING)

18:41.588 --> 18:44.122
Who wants breakfast?

18:44.124 --> 18:46.924
What is going on?

18:46.926 --> 18:48.326
No, don't let her...

18:48.328 --> 18:50.428
No, you can't, you...

18:50.430 --> 18:51.929
(LAUGHING)

18:51.931 --> 18:53.231
(CLUCKING)

18:53.233 --> 18:55.299
You guys know
what this is?

18:55.301 --> 18:57.068
Well, it looks like Diane

18:57.070 --> 18:59.370
has been leading a double
life as a real chicken!

18:59.372 --> 19:04.075
Yup. And it's our
ticket out of Aunt Lydia's
doghouse...

19:04.077 --> 19:06.210
literally.

19:08.480 --> 19:09.614
(SNIFFING)

19:09.616 --> 19:10.648
Going somewhere?

19:10.650 --> 19:13.050
(CLUCKING IN ALARM)
Diane!

19:13.052 --> 19:15.019
(TERRIFIED CLUCKING)

19:15.021 --> 19:18.656
I'm very disappointed.

19:18.658 --> 19:21.959
Adequate work, Mavis.

19:22.227 --> 19:23.861
So, that was awful.

19:23.863 --> 19:27.865
Yeah. Telling on Diane didn't
feel as good as I'd hoped.

19:27.867 --> 19:32.103
Oh no! I can feel myself
getting drippier and drippier!

19:32.105 --> 19:34.405
The don't-sees!
It's happening!

19:34.407 --> 19:36.274
Come on!
Pull yourself together!

19:36.276 --> 19:39.277
With Diane on doody duty,
we're free to cross
that bridge

19:39.279 --> 19:43.447
and catch the last episode
of <i>Hotel Pennsylvania!</i>

19:44.583 --> 19:48.586
WENDY:
So, I guess you don't
know your Aunt?

19:49.254 --> 19:52.256
The puddling has begun!

19:52.258 --> 19:53.758
Uh-oh, here it comes.

19:53.760 --> 19:57.528
We're in for
the clucking of a lifetime.

19:57.530 --> 20:00.898
(CLUCKING DEJECTEDLY)

20:00.999 --> 20:02.600
What was that?

20:02.602 --> 20:04.435
Huh.
Is it possible

20:04.437 --> 20:08.706
Diane actually misses
hanging out with the humans?

20:11.710 --> 20:14.278
Diane. It's me, Mavis.

20:14.280 --> 20:18.049
I know you don't have
any reason to trust me,

20:18.051 --> 20:19.817
but I'm really sorry

20:19.819 --> 20:23.621
for messing up your weird,
weird thing with the humans.

20:23.623 --> 20:24.589
(CLUCKING)

20:24.591 --> 20:25.823
I want to make it up to you.

20:25.825 --> 20:30.928
I think if we work together,
there's a way everybody wins.

20:30.930 --> 20:31.862
(CLUCKING)

20:31.864 --> 20:34.599
Okay, team,
we're running out of time.

20:34.601 --> 20:36.500
We must watch TV!

20:36.502 --> 20:38.135
So, leave the talking to me.

20:38.137 --> 20:41.038
I'm an excellent negotiator.

20:41.406 --> 20:43.808
(CLEARING THROAT)

20:44.209 --> 20:46.110
(ALL SCREAMING)

20:46.378 --> 20:48.346
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

20:48.747 --> 20:51.983
Don't look at me! I'm hideous!

20:51.985 --> 20:52.917
Wait a sec!

20:52.919 --> 20:56.954
I have wings!
I can just fly over
and then...

20:58.123 --> 20:59.357
Oh, come on!

20:59.359 --> 21:03.194
Guys, this is just like that
<i>Hotel Pennsylvania</i> episode

21:03.196 --> 21:08.299
when Davis, Tank,
and Petra had to escape...

21:08.301 --> 21:10.001
(SIGHING)
Let's just dig a tunnel.

21:10.003 --> 21:11.502
Yeah, great thinking!
Nice one!

21:11.504 --> 21:14.538
You da blob, Wendy!
(CLUCKING)

21:17.142 --> 21:20.311
(GASPING)
Made it!

21:20.313 --> 21:22.079
I'm so excited!

21:22.081 --> 21:23.881
Ooh-ooh-ooh!

21:23.883 --> 21:25.850
Oh, gosh...

21:26.918 --> 21:29.587
(CROWING)

21:29.589 --> 21:33.891
You're back.
You're back! You're back!

21:33.893 --> 21:37.228
Oh! Oh, joyous day!

21:37.230 --> 21:38.629
We were so worried!

21:38.631 --> 21:41.632
Humans are just gross.

21:41.634 --> 21:43.134
She did it though.

21:43.136 --> 21:45.703
They're totally
distracted by her!

21:45.705 --> 21:46.771
Even <i>Hotel Pennsylvania</i>

21:46.773 --> 21:49.173
couldn't have thought up
a moment like this!

21:49.175 --> 21:53.177
Now, let's go watch
the finale!

21:53.378 --> 21:56.781
And once again,
TV saves lives.

21:56.783 --> 21:59.317
(ALL SIGHING)

21:59.319 --> 22:01.052
<i>♪ And me and me</i>

22:01.054 --> 22:04.922
<i>♪ At Hotel Pennsylvania</i>
<i>(LAUGHING)</i>

22:07.492 --> 22:10.161
<i>♪</i>
